These directories contain needed files and specifications for the different networking hardware supported by the installation.

Each hardware directory may include the following:

1. adapter.conf

Identification and installation details for the hardware.

HARDWARE_MODEL. Formal identifier.
HARDWARE_NAME. Descriptive string.

2. notes.README

Useful installation documentation and commentary. Build instructions for modules.

3. /modules directory with required pre-built kernel files (extension .ko).

Drivers specific to the hardware. 

4. dependencies

Listing of deb dependencies, of which each line has the following format:

<Package name> <Deb file name>

When packages depend on other packages, order the deepest dependency before the others.
